## Phase 1 – Object Storage Foundation

**Filesystem Concepts:** Content-addressable storage, directory sharding, atomic writes, hashing for integrity  
**Files implemented:** `object.c` — `object_write`, `object_read`

### Implementation Summary

`object_write` prepends a type header (`blob <size>\0`, `tree <size>\0`, or `commit <size>\0`) to the data, computes a SHA-256 hash of the full content, and writes the object atomically using a temp-file-then-rename pattern. Objects are sharded into subdirectories by the first two hex characters of the hash.

`object_read` reads the file at the hashed path, parses the header to extract type and size, recomputes the SHA-256 to verify integrity against the filename, and returns the data portion after the null byte.

