## Phase 3 – The Index (Staging Area)

**Filesystem Concepts:** File format design, atomic writes, change detection using metadata  
**Files implemented:** `index.c` — `index_load`, `index_save`, `index_add`

### Implementation Summary

`index_load` reads `.pes/index` line by line, parsing each entry in the format `<mode> <hash-hex> <mtime> <size> <path>`. If the file doesn't exist, it initializes an empty index without error.

`index_save` sorts all entries by path, writes them to a temp file, calls `fsync()`, then atomically renames the temp file to `.pes/index`.

`index_add` reads the target file, computes its blob and writes it to the object store via `object_write`, then creates or updates the index entry with the current `mtime`, `size`, and hash.

